label("$B$", B, S);
label("$C$", C, S);
label("$D$", D, N);
label("$M$", M, S);
[/asy]

Let $AD = CD = x.$  Then by the Law of Cosines on triangle $ABC,$
\[21^2 = 9^2 + x^2 - 2 \cdot 9 \cdot x \cos \angle ACB.\]Hence,
\[\cos \angle ACB = \frac{9^2 + x^2 - 21^2}{2 \cdot 9 \cdot x} = \frac{x^2 - 144}{18x}.\]Also, $\cos \angle ACD = -\cos \angle ACB,$ so
\[\cos \angle ACD = \frac{144 - x^2}{18x}.\]By the Law of Cosines on triangle $ACD,$
\[x^2 = 9^2 + \left( \frac{s - 9 - 21 - 2x}{2} \right)^2 - (s - 9 - 21 - 2x) \cdot \frac{144 - x^2}{18x}.\]This simplifies to
\[x^4 - 36x^3 + 324x^2 - (s - 60)x - 3s + 1356 = 0.\]Note that $x$ is a factor of $3s - 1356.$  If $x = 9,$ then $ABCD$ is a parallelogram, so $AD = 21,$ which is impossible.  Hence, $x \ge 10.$

If $x = 10,$ then $s = 2(9 + 10 + 21) = 80.$

If $x = 12,$ then $s = 2(9 + 12 + 21) + 2(10 + 12 + 21) = 114.$

If $x = 18,$ then $s = 2(9 + 18 + 21) + 2(10 + 18 + 21) = 126.$

Thus, $s = \boxed{320}.$

